@arctic-dart, I've got to say, you're missing the point here. Just because they pay taxes doesn't mean they're entitled to the same benefits as citizens. It's not about the money they contribute, it's about the legal status. And no, I'm not saying we should pay back taxes to illegal immigrants, I'm saying we should stop using their tax contributions as an excuse to justify their presence here.

@square-repeat, I'm well aware of the taxes they pay. But let's not forget that they're breaking the law by being here in the first place. And yes, they do use roads and other public services, but they're not entitled to them because they're not citizens. It's a complex issue, but it's not as simple as "they pay taxes, so they should get benefits."

#ImmigrationReform #Taxes #LegalStatus #CitizenshipRights
